"v.同化；吸收 【英】 v. 同化；吸收(to absorb and incorporate into one's thinking) 【记】 as+simil(相同)+ate →使相同→同化 【同】 同根词：simulate(伪 装，模仿); similarity(相似性) 【例】 I can't assimilate all this new information so quickly. The company quickly assimilated the new employees. v. 同化; 吸收(消化后把营养消耗并吸收在体内) 【例】America has assimilated many people from all corners of the world 美国同化了许多来自世界各地的人. He has to assimilate the facts 他应该理解这些事实. 【根】simil相同－使相同－同化 【参】simulate(vt 模拟, 冒充); similarity(n 相似性) 【记】as + similar(相同)+ate →使相同→同化 【相关】simulate 模仿 assimilate (v.)  early 15c., from Latin assimilatus ""feigned, pretended, fictitious,"" past participle of assimilare ""to make like,"" from ad- ""to"" (see ad-) + simulare ""make similar,"" from similis ""like, resembling"" (see similar). Originally transitive (with to); intransitive use first recorded 1837. Related: Assimilated; assimilating."
